article.headline: Delaware State 50, Norfolk State 47
article.story: DOVER, Del. (AP) -- Jahsha Bluntt scored 10 points and finished off a late run that carried Delaware State past Norfolk State 50-47 on Monday night. Terrance Hunter and Darrin Shine added nine points each for the Hornets (7-11, 5-2 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference), who won their third straight. Trailing 21-18 at halftime, Delaware State began the second half with a 16-2 run to take a 34-23 lead with 12:31 left. But Norfolk State responded with a 16-2 run of its own and led 39-36 with 6:03 remaining. The Hornets pulled back ahead with an 11-3 run, taking a 47-42 lead on a layup by Bluntt with 1:56 remaining. They led 50-44 before Armand Massogo's 3-pointer at the buzzer. Karandick Ogunride had 13 points and 15 rebounds for the Spartans (8-8, 6-2), who saw their six-game conference winning streak snapped. Chakowby Hicks added 11 points. Delaware State shot just 32.1 percent from the field but scored 24 points off 20 Norfolk State turnovers. Both teams were awful from the free-throw line, with each shooting 44.4 percent.
